strings:
<voice_0x01000D1D><se_def>*: ...Nine 'undred 'n' ninety eight...nine 'undred 'n' ninety nine...nine 'undred 'n' ninety...er...oh, yeah!
A grand! Sweet!

<voice_0x01000D1E><se_def>*: He knows 'is stuff, that ol' merchant!
He could see 'ow much it was werf.

<voice_0x01000D1F><se_def>*: Half-inchin' that 'orse was a piece o' cake!
Easy dosh, Mitts, eh! Easy dosh! He he heh!

<voice_0x01000D20><se_def>Mitts: Eh!? W-Who's that!? Oh, no!
You ain't the owner of that 'orse, is ya!?
<voice_0x01000D21><se_low>King Trode: So it was you! You're the scoundrel responsible for taking the Princess!

<voice_0x01000D22><se_def>Mitts: Wot the 'ell!?
Get that monster away from me!
Wot's it on about? Wot princess?
I only knocked off a horse!

<voice_0x01000D23><se_low>King Trode: Who are you calling a monster!?
Give my Medea back right now or
suffer the consequences!

<voice_0x01000D24><se_def>Mitts: Easy! Take it easy! I swear!
I didn't know! I didn't know it was no
monster princess or nuffin'!

<voice_0x01000D25><se_def>Mitts: Here...'ave it all!
This is all the dough I got for it, I swear!
Just don't 'urt me!

<voice_0x01000D26><se_low>King Trode: What!? You sold my daughter!?
That's it! <Cap><hero>!
Slay this worthless wastrel!

<voice_0x01000D27><se_low>Yangus: Hold yer 'orses, Grandad! Sorry...I mean,
take it easy. This toerag ain't good enough
for the guv's sword.

<voice_0x01000D28><se_low>Yangus: Awright, you! Let's 'ear it!
Sell it down beggars' alley, did ya?
To ol' Dodgy Dave, eh?

<voice_0x01000D29><se_def>Mitts: Y-Yeah, that's it...
Know 'im, do ya?

<voice_0x01000D2A><se_low>Yangus: Right then, 'and over the dough!
If I find out you've been tellin' me porkies,
you're brown bread, d'you 'ear?

<voice_0x01000D2B><se_def>Mitts: Look, I ain't been lyin', mister, I swear!
Here...a thousand gold pieces!
That's wot 'e gimme for it!
<voice_0x01000D2C><se_low>Yangus: No need to worry! The black market geezer 'e was talkin' about is a mate o' mine.
<voice_0x01000D2D><se_low>Yangus: He'll give us back the 'orse-princess if we give 'im back the dough! ...I mean, money.

<voice_0x01000D2E><se_low>King Trode: Then why are we dallying around here!?
We must go to this ‘geezer's’ shop immediately!
